data.text:
Programming rated TV-Y7 in the United States TV Parental Guidelines signifies content that is suitable for children 7 years and older but under adult age. Many of these programs contain some fantasy violence. Most shows on Disney XD, NickToons, Universal Kids, and Cartoon Network (Except some shows such as Adventure Time and Steven Universe) have received this rating. Notable shows that got this rating are SpongeBob SquarePants (Newer episodes), The Loud House, Foster‘s Home for Imaginary Friends, Big City Greens, WordGirl and The 2017 Reboot of DuckTales. Equivalent to hard G for movies and hard E for video games.

Content descriptors[]

FV: Fantasy Violence (The only one used, and only used for this rating.) This is used to indicate that a TV-Y7 rated program contains behavior that is more intense and/or combative but is however fictional and can be shown to children who understand the difference between fantasy and reality.
